 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "NonwovenAdvisor ⊣ Nonwoven & Technical Textiles Plant Operations
 Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for ISIC 1399 (Manufacture of other
 textiles n.e.c.) -- a residual textile category (e.g. nonwovens,
 felt, tire-cord fabric, technical/industrial textiles) distinct from
 siblings 1392/1393/1394. This build's own chosen concrete
 illustration is nonwoven/felt fabric manufacturing (needle-punched,
 spunbond, or meltblown forming lines bonded into nonwoven fabric or
 felt) -- not direct forming/bonding-line control authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Twelve concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's four HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (no direct forming-line
 or bonding-line control), permanent direct-operate block, independent
 equipment verification/registration before maintenance scheduling,
 independent batch verification/registration before shipment
 coordination, independent shipment-area recompute against the
 batch's own logged area, double-schedule guard, quality-grade
 validation, tensile-strength-test plausibility validation,
 basis-weight-test plausibility validation, and defect-rate
 plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging (equipment-safety /
 quality-defect) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor;
 `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
